Season: 1940

12/28/1940; Nacional; 2-2; Boca Juniors; Montevideo, Uruguay
Notes: abandonded at 2-2 after 90 minutes; Boca Juniors left the field, Nacional declared the winner.
* But, AUF asked to AFA to study the situation on Jan 22, 1941 and no decision was taken.

Season: 1941 
* The title to be defined in two legs. If the teams tied in points: Both clubs would be the champions.  The cup would be held by the association whose team had scored more goals.

5/29/1942; River Plate; 6-1; Nacional; Buenos Aires, Argentina

12/5/1942; Nacional; 1-1; River Plate; Montevideo, Uruguay


Season: 1942

12/8/1942; Nacional; 4-0; River Plate; Montevideo, Uruguay
Notes: The second leg was not played and the title was not officially proclaimed.


